Callum,



Unfortunately, a member of staff at Cornwall Wildlife Trust was the victim of a phishing attack this morning, and the attacker then used the victims account to send out more phishing messages.  I’ve analysed the list and 77 of those emails went to Mounts Bay Academy so I thought I should contact you.



The details of the email are below, the infrastructure used by the attacker is flagged by Microsoft as being used for ‘Attacker in the Middle’ phishing, which is where the authentication by the victim is proxied by the attacker who can then steal authentication cookies, allowing them to bypass Multi-Factor Authentication.  If any of your accounts are compromised as well as revoking all existing login sessions and resetting the password, I would also check for recently added Multi-Factor methods, as those could be used to regain control of the account after the password is reset.



Email details

Sender: Lucy.Luck@cornwallwildlifetrust.org.uk

Subject: THE CORNWALL TRUST FOR NATURE CONSERVATION LIMITED

Date/time: 10th August 10:15am

Payload: an email attachment (EML file) links to a Word Online document which in turn links to a phishing URL (more details available if required).



Cheers

Good afternoon,

I had a really lovely meeting with Karl and Josie from the wellbeing team
today. The team is looking forward to moving in on September 25th.

I have discussed the following with the team if any of this is a problem
please let me know, otherwise please action:

Site team

   - Arrange for installation of two additional double sockets on the back
   wall
   - If we have any spare the installation of notice boards - If we don't
   they will order some
   - 9 Keys for the team - they come and go at different times
   - 8 desks to go around the perimeter wall
   - Install the new room sign on the door (It's currently in my office)
   - If we can rustle up some sort of coffee table or meeting table for the
   middle of the room they would be very grateful

IT/Holly

   - Set up a guest account for photocopying "NHSWellbeing team" with the
   papercut monthly report coming to me for monthly recharging
   - Check the wi-fi access in the room and pass on guest wi-fi access
   details to myself - Ideally longer codes than a month (It is the currently
   empty room in the exams block)

Jacqui

   - Please can the team have a pigeon hole as they will be receiving post
   - The team will all have a DBS, please can you let me know all the
   details required for visitors on the SCR and we'll make sure you have them
   prior to them starting.

Misc

   - The team is going to drop off laptops - these can be stored in my
   office until their secure storage arrives
   - I will meet with the team on their first day to go through fire,
   lockdown, building, car park/bike procedures etc.
   - Josie, the admin manager, is arranging for chairs and lockable storage
   to be ordered and delivered here - she will let us know when delivery is
   expected.
   - I will set up accounts on ParentPay so the team can access school
   lunches

Thanks very much
Sam

*Hope you are well.*

*This is a quick note to confirm we will be turning up at your provided

above-booked date between **8-3pm**.*

/ok for collection to go ahead.*

*     B.*                *If you have a loose collection, please advise

code.*

any interactive boards, smart tv or whiteboards ready for collection.*

*     F.        Please ensure bins/cages or items being collected are moved
to an easily accessible area for a prompt and efficient collection.*



*Please endeavor to respond/complete this confirmation** at least a day
before the day of your collection to avoid any possible disappointment or
delays.*

*All things being equal we will see you on the day of your collection.*

*Kind Regards.*

ENVIRO ELECTRONICS.
